20:12.068 --> 20:18.162
Meditation is the practice of coming to God's word again and again and again.

20:18.626 --> 20:31.647
And it's more than just reading the words, it's taking the time to truly listen to what they're saying, to understand the instructions that are given, to take in the truth of those words, to take the encouragement that they give.

20:32.268 --> 20:43.986
Like memorizing our favorite song, meditation turns our hearts to the tune of what God wants to say directly to us and how he wants to fill our lives.

20:44.258 --> 20:51.508
He invites us to dive into scripture so deeply to know him so that it becomes a part of us.

20:54.251 --> 21:00.300
You know, meditation isn't about committing chapters and chapters to memory, the Bible to memory.

21:00.420 --> 21:02.643
I mean, that might be the result at some point.

21:04.365 --> 21:11.835
It is choosing a single verse or two and diving deeper into their meeting, just like we did earlier today.

21:11.855 --> 21:14.098
I read the verse.

21:15.042 --> 21:16.224
We sat with it for a moment.

21:17.365 --> 21:18.046
I read it again.

21:18.066 --> 21:21.811
We sat with it, and then we asked questions.

21:22.712 --> 21:24.334
Is there a word that stood out to me?

21:25.435 --> 21:27.438
Is there a phrase that caught my attention?

21:28.379 --> 21:30.642
Is there an action that I'm called to do?

21:30.682 --> 21:39.053
Is there something in this verse that can change the way that I live or the way that I think or the way that I love today?

21:41.596 --> 21:43.218
Meditation is powerful.

21:43.714 --> 21:56.112
It's thinking and processing, even writing it down and certainly saying the words over and over to ourselves so that we hear the word of God speak.

21:58.496 --> 22:03.643
When we meditate, we hear the word of God speak.

22:03.663 --> 22:13.618
Now I wanna tell you that throughout my years in ministry, I cannot begin to tell you how many times I have heard people say they don't get anything out of the Bible when they read it.

22:15.330 --> 22:16.992
People say, I don't understand it.

22:18.734 --> 22:19.595
I think it's boring.

22:21.257 --> 22:22.779
It is outdated.

22:24.541 --> 22:25.382
It's too harsh.

22:27.585 --> 22:29.167
It's hard to believe.

22:31.430 --> 22:32.731
I don't understand that language.

22:34.734 --> 22:36.996
And the list goes on and on and on.

22:38.418 --> 22:43.144
And maybe they've tried to read it once or twice, but man, they hit that first little phrase that doesn't make sense.

22:43.164 --> 22:44.205
And they're like, I'm out.

22:44.626 --> 22:44.946
Let's go.

22:47.234 --> 22:55.106
But let those saying people, and we are those people, by the way, let those saying people get in their car and turn on the radio.

22:56.729 --> 22:59.253
You're the meaning in my life.

22:59.633 --> 23:03.079
You're the inspiration, right?

23:03.139 --> 23:03.519
