24:47.679 --> 24:51.584
You want roots that go down deep, get your face in the word.

24:52.366 --> 24:54.048
You want a life that's gonna prosper.

24:54.088 --> 24:56.352
You want a life that's gonna be obedient.

24:56.672 --> 24:58.034
You know God's truth.

24:58.818 --> 25:06.489
You want a tree that's fruitful, that leaves don't wither or fade, then you plant your feet firmly in God's Word.

25:06.509 --> 25:10.114
And you have it course through your veins.

25:12.338 --> 25:13.139
That's how we know.

25:13.159 --> 25:16.243
If you're gonna clap, just clap, come on, let's do it.

25:17.605 --> 25:19.448
It is the Word of God we're talking about here.

25:19.508 --> 25:26.258
The benefits of delighting and meditating result in the life of fruitfulness.

25:27.906 --> 25:29.268
Y'all want some good fruit?

25:29.288 --> 25:33.754
I don't want to be a wilted up nasty looking old tree with shriveled up prunes on it.

25:35.957 --> 25:37.339
I'm old, but I'm not that old.

25:38.781 --> 25:39.442
So I do yoga.

25:43.047 --> 25:47.954
There is beautiful fruit in our lives.

25:48.546 --> 25:51.790
when we take in God's word, when we let him speak to us.

25:52.151 --> 25:54.694
There's a beautiful example of this in the New Testament.

25:55.214 --> 25:58.839
In Luke chapter 10, two sisters, Mary and Martha, you remember them?

25:59.980 --> 26:02.804
And they had a brother named Lazarus, there you go.

26:03.164 --> 26:04.807
So Jesus comes to visit them.

26:05.347 --> 26:09.412
And Martha, the oldest sister who is technically the owner of the house, by the way.

26:11.395 --> 26:13.938
She's busy, y'all, she's making a meal, she's in it.

26:14.690 --> 26:19.697
And she notices that Mary, her younger sister, has gone into the room to sit down.

26:19.737 --> 26:21.359
And Jesus is in there teaching.

26:21.800 --> 26:23.542
So Mary just kind of makes her way over.

26:23.602 --> 26:25.044
And she's sitting down.

26:25.164 --> 26:27.928
And Martha's over here like, whoo, apron on, going for it.

26:28.389 --> 26:30.391
And look what she says in Luke 10, chapter 40.

26:30.692 --> 26:34.597
But Martha was distracted by the big dinner she was preparing.

26:34.657 --> 26:44.050
She came to Jesus and said, Lord, doesn't it seem unfair to you that my sister just sits here while I do all the work?

26:44.706 --> 26:45.928
Tell her to come and help me.

26:45.968 --> 26:49.232
Tell her to come and help me.

26:51.635 --> 27:00.647
And Jesus looks at her and says, Martha, Martha, you can hear the tenderness in his voice.

27:03.151 --> 27:11.843
He says, you are worried and upset and distracted by many things.

27:13.665 --> 27:14.386
Only one thing.

27:15.682 --> 27:16.163
It's needed.

27:20.969 --> 27:24.573
I've got to admit to you today, I'm a Martha.

27:27.176 --> 27:30.120
Many of you here today, probably a Martha.

27:34.205 --> 27:35.467
Truth is most of us are Martha.

27:36.408 --> 27:41.795
And Martha was living from what she did, rather than who she was.

27:43.357 --> 27:44.498
And it was exhausting her.

27:45.986 --> 27:47.467
Anybody in here today exhausted?

27:50.310 --> 27:51.671
Perhaps you know what that feels like.

27:52.412 --> 27:59.579
We define ourselves by our productivity, our usefulness, our ability to get things done.

27:59.639 --> 28:08.688
